<p style="margin: 0px;">You may be able to take advantage of a work arrangement that gives you flexibility in balancing your life and work schedules. Flexible work arrangements are mutually agreed upon by a manager and an associate.</p>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 6px 0px;"><span class="body2">Work arrangement options</span></p>
<ul>
	<li><b>FlexTime.</b> The opportunity to alter starting and/or departure times</li>
	<li><b>Compressed workweeks.</b> Condenses a full-time workweek into fewer days</li>
	<li><b>Telecommuting.</b> The ability to perform all or part of your work from a location other than your normal work site</li>
	<li><b>Select time.</b> Reduces your work schedule and job responsibilities for a specific need</li>
	<li><b>Phase-in.</b> The option to gradually return to a regular work schedule after a medical leave</li>
</ul>
